description: Lodestar framework rules for {{PROJECT_NAME}}
alwaysApply: true
---

This project follows the Lodestar framework.

- Read `PROJECT.md` (stage, mode, north star) and `.lodestar/SPEC.md` (full spec)
  before working. Follow `AGENTS.md`.
- Lifecycle: `1-discovery → 2-design → 3-build → 4-operate`; the stage is the
  directory.
- Keep the north star in view; surface conflicts instead of proceeding.
- Write outputs to the correct stage folder with frontmatter + `parent:` link.
- Never skip a stage silently — log the reason in
  `docs/99-decision-research/gate-skips/` and update `PROJECT.md`.
- Implementation tasks trace to a User Story; include `TASK-NNN` in commits.
